│ /// Utility class for getting and setting loop vectorizer hints in the form of                                               │
│ /// loop metadata.                                                                                                           │
│ /// This class is a wrapper around the MDNode which holds the hints. It makes it                                             │
│ /// easy to read and write the vectorization hints.                                                                          │
│ /// The LoopVectorize pass uses this class to set the hints for the vector                                                   │
│ iled                                                                                                                         │
│ /// loop. The LoopVectorize pass and other passes can use this class to query                                                │
│ /// the hints.                                                                                                               │
│ ///                                                                                                                          │
│ /// The hints are stored in a MDNode with the following format:                                                              │
│ ///                                                                                                                          │
│ ///   !{!"llvm.loop.vectorize.width", i32 <width>}                                                                           │
│ ///   !{!"llvm.loop.vectorize.scalable.enable", i1 <enable>}                                                                 │
│ ///                                                                                                                          │
│ /// The <width> hint is the vectorization factor.                                                                            │
│ /// The <enable> hint is a boolean indicating if the loop is vectorized.                                                     │
│ ///                                                                                                                          │
│ /// If <width> is 1, the loop is not vectorized.                                                                             │
│ /// If <width> is 0, the loop is not vectorized and the vectorizer should not                                                │
│ /// try to vectorize it.                                                                                                     │
│ /// If <width> is > 1, the loop is vectorized with that factor.                                                              │
│ ///                                                                                                                          │
│ /// If <scalable.enable> is true, the loop is vectorized with a scalable vector                                              │
│ /// size. In this case, the <width> hint is the minimum vectorization factor.                                                │
│ /// If <scalable.enable> is false, the loop is vectorized with a fixed vector                                                │
│ /// size.                                                                                                                    │
│ ///                                                                                                                          │
│ /// The LoopVectorize pass may also add other hints to the loop metadata.                                                    │
│ /// These hints are not part of the public API and may change in the future.                                                 │
│ /// They are stored in the same MDNode as the public hints.                                                                  │
│ /// The format of these hints is:                                                                                            │
│ ///                                                                                                                          │
│ ///   !{!"llvm.loop.vectorize.followup_vectorized", !"<loop_id>"}                                                            │
│ ///                                                                                                                          │
│ /// The "followup_vectorized" hint is a string containing the loop ID of the                                                 │
